The paper proposes a new algorithm for online learning with graph-structured sparsity constraints, which is a problem commonly studied in machine learning and optimization. The paper focuses on convex objective functions and uses dual space projection to capture graph-structured sparsity effectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also conducts experiments on graph datasets, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
